        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Adding to this a bit, I could imagine adding collection specific information to layers.  For arrays this might be chunks and dtype, for dataframes this might be partition structure, columns, and dtypes.  \r\n\r\nDoing this is a little bit odd.  It adds information that is normally orthogonal onto the graph.  This breaks a bit of cleanliness.  It also might be an interesting step forward.  We might start using this strictly for visualization, and then later on decide that it's useful for other things, like optimization.  I don't anticipate this being deleterious in any way, assuming that when we serialize the graph that we don't bother sending this information just yet.  \r\n\r\nThis would allow us to provide much richer visualizations though, including things like column names and chunk structure for different stages in the graph.",
