        "body": "I, for one, would *love* a variant of the .visualize() method that \r\n\r\n1. stops at layer level, thus producing a much terser graph\r\n2. in the corner of the box of each layer, it tells me the number of output keys\r\n3. differentiates with color/shapes\r\n    - embarassingly parallel layers\r\n    - reduction layers\r\n    - \"ghost\" layers (where a chunk needs access to the immediate neighbours)\r\n    - more sophisticated layers\r\n4. big-O complexity, both inside each chunk and between chunks",
